com.zhuinden.simplestack

Class Backstack

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.zhuinden.simplestack.Backstack

  • public class Backstack
extends java.lang.Object
    The Backstack holds the current state, in the form of a list of Objects. It queues up StateChanges while a StateChanger is not available. When a StateChanger is available, it attempts to execute the queued StateChanges. A StateChanger can be either set to INITIALIZE, or to REATTACH. INITIALIZE begins an initializing StateChange to set up initial state, REATTACH does not.

      • replaceTop

        public void replaceTop(java.lang.Object newTop,
                       int direction)
        Replaces the current top with the provided key. This means removing the current last element, and then adding the new element.
        Parameters:
        newTop - the new top key
        direction - The direction of the StateChange: StateChange.BACKWARD, StateChange.FORWARD or StateChange.REPLACE.

      • goUp

        public void goUp(java.lang.Object newKey)
        Goes "up" to the provided element. This means that if the provided element is found anywhere in the history, then the history goes to it. If not found, then the current top is replaced with the provided element. Going up occurs in StateChange.BACKWARD direction.
        Parameters:
        newKey - the new key to go up to

      • goUpChain

        public void goUpChain(java.util.List<java.lang.Object> parentChain)
        Goes "up" once to the provided chain of parents. If the chain of parents is found as previous elements, then it works as back navigation to that chain. If the whole chain is not found, but at least one element of it is found, then the history is kept up to that point, then the chain is added, any duplicate element in the chain is added to the end as part of the chain. If no element of the chain is found in the history, then the current top is removed, and the provided parent chain is added in its place. Going up the chain occurs in StateChange.BACKWARD direction.
        Parameters:
        parentChain - the chain of parents, from oldest to newest.

      • goBack

        public boolean goBack()
        Goes back in the history. If the key is found, then it goes backward to the existing key. If the key is not found, then it goes forward to the newly added key.
        Returns:
        true if a state change is pending or is handled with a state change, false if there is only one state left.

      • reset

        public void reset()
        Immediately clears the backstack, it is NOT enqueued as a state change. If there are pending state changes, then it throws an exception. You generally don't need to use this method.

      • executePendingStateChange

        public void executePendingStateChange()
        If there is a state change in progress, then calling this method will force it to be completed immediately. Any future calls to StateChanger.Callback.stateChangeComplete() for that given state change are ignored.
